Tectonic is currently seeking a part-time Environmental Project Monitor to perform work primarily within the Hudson Valley, NY area on an as-needed basis.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

Essential functions of the Environmental Project Monitor position require traveling to project sites to serve as the on-site representative to oversee asbestos abatement work to ensure that work is performed in accordance with specifications and in compliance with all Federal, State, and local laws. In addition, the Project Monitor will perform air monitoring in accordance with all applicable regulations, which includes performing monitoring with pumps and cartridges, collecting air samples during abatement projects, preparing and maintaining chain of custody data. delivering air samples to the laboratory, and performing aggressive air monitoring when necessary. 

In addition, the Environmental Project Monitor must maintain project logs and reports, take photographs as needed, record applicable data, and communicate with project managers, contractors, and/or client representatives, as well as all related duties as assigned. 

TO VIEW AND APPLY, PLEASE VISIT: 

QUALIFICATIONS

•Valid NYS DOL Project Monitor and Air Sampling Technician Certifications;
•2 years of related experience performing project monitoring and/or air sampling on abatement projects;
•Bachelor’s Degree in Environmental Science or a related field is a plus; HS Diploma/Equivalent required;
•Ability to complete OSHA 10 Hour Construction Safety and Health Training within a reasonable period of time;
•Functional computer skills, including familiarity with Microsoft Outlook, Word and Excel, as well as ability to utilize various software programs, time reporting systems, and other related computer applications;
•Strong interpersonal skills, with effective oral and written communication skills;
•Possession of own air monitoring equipment is a plus;
•Valid driver’s license and personal vehicle for regular travel to project sites.

We are an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer, and highly encourage resumes from all interested parties including women, minorities, veterans and persons with disabilities. All qualified applicants will be afforded equal employment opportunities without discrimination on the basis of race, creed, color, national origin, sex, age, disability, marital status, or any other protected class.

Tectonic participates in the USCIS E-Verify Program to verify that all new hires are authorized to work in the United States.
